title: MAR 21 2022 - WAR IN UKRAINE - DAY 26 UPDATE
description:
Ukrainian President, Volodymyr Zelensky, suspends 11 political parties with links to Russia, and signs a decree to combine national TV channels into one federal platform citing martial law. Meanwhile, four U.S. marines are killed in Norway during a NATO drill. Over two years into the coronavirus, official figures may have overestimated Britain’s coronavirus death toll, and the leader of Mexico’s Northeast drug cartel, El Huevo, was turned over to U.S. authorities and faces multiple charges that could imprison him for life. 

Here’s your Daily dose of Human Events with @JackPosobiec
